negotiating an end to its nuclear weapons program practically unachievable after years of denying even any interest in uranium enrichment north korea has lost what little credibility its statements had furthermore argued straub by secretly building the facility in yongbyon the one location that outsiders watch most closely north korea itself has proven there is no way that outsiders could verify a nuclear agreement radio free asia korean language transcript fundamental reform or regime change the only options search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest straub on us north korea nuclear agreement march 1 2012 shorenstein aparc ksp news straub discusses north korean leadership succession january 9 2012 shorenstein aparc ksp news as tripoli falls a political scientist says a difficult road lies ahead august 24 2011 cisac fsi stanford in the news inspectors would see only part of the picture in north korea says straub shorenstein aparc ksp in the news voice of america korean service on january 3 2011 north korea and the sinking of the south korean navy vessel cheonan may 19 2010 shorenstein aparc ksp news david straub joins clinton delegation to north korea to secure release of current tv journalists august 10 2009 fsi stanford shorenstein aparc ksp in the news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
